Debugging= identify and fix problem..

1. Set a Breakpoint
Open your Python file
Click on the left margin (next to line numbers)
A red dot 🔴 will appear → this is a breakpoint

👉 It tells PyCharm: “Stop execution here”

▶️ 2. Run in Debug Mode
Click the bug icon 🐞 (top right), or
Press Shift + F9

👉 Your program will start and pause at the breakpoint

🔍 3. Debug Window (Main Tools)

When execution stops, you’ll see:

➤ Variables Panel
Shows current values of variables
Helps you check if values are correct or wrong
➤ Console
Shows output and errors
⏭️ 4. Control Execution

These buttons are very important:

Step Over (F8)
→ Run next line (skip inside functions)
Step Into (F7)
→ Go inside a function
Step Out (Shift + F8)
→ Exit current function
Resume (F9)
→ Continue until next breakpoint
🧠 5. Watch Variables (Optional)
Right-click a variable → Add to Watches
Track its value changes step by step
⚠️ 6. Common Debug Use Cases

✔ Check wrong output
✔ Find logical errors
✔ Track variable values
✔ Understand program flow

🔥 Example
x = 10
y = 0
z = x / y   # breakpoint here
print(z)

👉 Run debugger → it stops before error
👉 You can inspect x and y
👉 You’ll quickly see division by zero problem
